title: For Sale:  NIB Sampson Evolution 7 Rail System
postcontent:
The Samson Manufacturing Evolution Series free float rails are customizable AR-15 handguards. The Evo rail attaches to a standard barrel nut with a two piece thermal bushing constructed of stainless steel, two locking tabs ensure the rail does not rotate under stress. The thermal bushing along with the generous ventilation slots help to keep heat from transferring into the handguard and into the operator's hand. The continuous top rail allows you to mount optics anywhere along the top of the rifle and allows same-plane iron sights to be mounted. The top rail has also been relieved to accept most aftermarket piston conversion systems. Each Evo handguard includes two 2", and one 4" customizable rail sections that can be mounted anywhere along the handguard tube. The interior of the tube is 1.56" in diameter, allowing most suppressors to fit underneath.

The EVO Extended Rail series feature a front sight cut out, so the lower portion of the handguard extends out past the sides of the front sight post, giving you more mounting options on guns with shorter gas systems. The EX handguards are the perfect choice for gas piston conversions.

Installation of the Evolution series handguards does not require special tools. Since the standard barrel nut (not included) is used to mount the handguard only the delta ring, weld spring and snap ring must be removed. This means you can install the EVO rail system without removing the barrel from the upper receiver, a step that requires specialized tools such as receiver blocks, barrel nut wrench or AR-15 multi-tool. The delta ring must be cut if you do not remove the barrel from the upper.

Technical Information :

    6010 T6 Aluminum Construction
    Mil-Spec Hard Coat Anodized Finish
    Uses Factory Barrel Nut (not included)
    303 Stainless Thermal bushing Reduces Heat Transfer
    Mil-Spec Picatinny Continuous Top Rail with Dual Alignment Tabs
    Relieved to Work with Aftermarket Piston Systems
    2x 2" 1x 4" Customizable Picatinny Rail Sections
    1.8" Outer Diameter (Facetted)
    1.56" Inner Diameter (Fits Most Suppressors)
    No Specialized Tools Required For Installation

title: For Sale/Trade:  WARNING!!HI-CAP MAG HOLDERS!!! THIS GUY DOESN'T KNOW WTF HE IS TALKING ABOUT
postcontent:
Ok so there is this guy selling 10rnd magpuls. And he keeps stating in his posts, "don't get cought with hi cap mags buy these the only legal magpuls in ca"
First and foremost this is a public information announcment for all those who own hi caps/oem mags.
In the state of California, the law states no persons other than police officers, government officials, and military may buy sell trade or be givin items classified as hi cap mags "ie. More than 10 rounds". 
That being said it is completely ""legal"" yes legal to own and use hi cap mags in the state of CA finding a range that will let you use them because they know the rules is a bit harder.
Furthermore, the statue of limitations on "building buying trading selling or importing for personal use" of hi caps is three years so if for some reason three years ago you bought some hi cap mag kits and put them together, yes you broke a law but, once you pass three years you cannot be charged the burden is on the investigators and Da to prove you committed the crime writhin the last three years. 
Also if you sign up and actually compete in competition shooting with any recognized shooting organization, then you are exempt from the law as having hi Cap mags would increase your chances of doing well in the competition.
That all said im in no way a legal deffence nor afilliated with any law group nor is any of this to be taken as legal advice, go about it yourself and read the laws "a few times" and remember it's the weird word of the law if it doesn't explicitly say you can't, then you can. Finding hi caps isnot illegal under any laws...
